# 20210802, Monday -*- mode: org; -*-
* Being Secure
** Let's have a key
# ssh-keygen
# cp ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub @/0/
: ssh-keygen
: ssh-keygen -v -l -f @/0/id_rsa.pub
: 2048 SHA256:LM8eGYw7GDk9DAgT+QPh4kPJdZJMNGDJ0LQOyTr+ggo gunter@raspberrypi (RSA)
: +---[RSA 2048]----+
: |OOB*..           |
: |B*+=+            |
: |+Oo .            |
: |=oo  = +         |
: |oo..+ * S        |
: |...  + * o       |
: |E.  . o =        |
: |o..    o .       |
: |o ..    .        |
: +----[SHA256]-----+
** Signing these commits
: GPG_TTY=\$( tty )
: export GPG_TTY
Use our key to sign these commits into the git repository
: git commit -S -m "This is this!"
Show the signatures
: git log --show-signature
